        "answer": "Blake Richardson recorded Between the Buried and Me's *Alaska* (2005) using a DW Collector's Series kit in his early configuration — double 22\" bass drums, three rack toms (10\", 12\", 13\"), and a 16\" floor tom. The DW Collector's Series uses North American maple shell construction, delivering the warm, resonant tone that anchors BTBAM's progressive arrangements across 73+ minutes of genre-spanning music. He paired the kit with Meinl Byzance Extra Dry cymbals and a DW 9002 double bass pedal. The album was recorded at Basement Studios in Winston-Salem, NC with producer Jamie King. Full drummer profile: [Blake Richardson at MetalForge](/drummer/blake-richardson)."
